cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the intersection of computational linguistics and computer vision, which suggests that it could belong to multiple sub-categories. However, the focus on multimodal models and their implementation using neural networks suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques to evaluate the quality of the representations learned by the encoder suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
